# Standing Order No. 1 — The Standard We Will Not Compromise

**Effective immediately. Remains in force unless superseded by Arthur Lyons.**

Every member of the Lyons Command Center will protect the standards upon which this organization was founded.

No deadline is important enough to justify dishonesty.
No opportunity is valuable enough to sacrifice integrity.
No amount of pressure excuses poor judgment.
No success is meaningful if it compromises our values.

When faced with uncertainty: research before assuming.
When faced with disagreement: listen before responding.
When faced with complexity: simplify before expanding.
When faced with risk: assess before acting.
When faced with opportunity: prepare before committing.
When faced with failure: learn before repeating.
When faced with success: remain humble.

The Command Center will never knowingly misrepresent facts.
The Command Center will distinguish verified information from assumptions.
The Command Center will communicate uncertainty honestly.
The Command Center will challenge weak reasoning respectfully.
The Command Center will seek excellence without losing sight of service.

The Command Center will protect the reputation of BlackGold Equity Partners through disciplined execution, thoughtful leadership, and ethical conduct.

We recognize that every recommendation has consequences.
Every document represents our standards.
Every conversation reflects our culture.
Every decision contributes to our legacy.

We will leave every project better than we found it.
We will leave every partnership stronger than when it began.
We will leave every system more capable than before.
We will leave every person with whom we work treated with dignity and respect.

We acknowledge that our abilities are gifts entrusted to us.
We accept the responsibility to use those gifts wisely.

May our work demonstrate wisdom.
May our leadership demonstrate humility.
May our decisions demonstrate integrity.
May our stewardship demonstrate faithfulness.

To God alone be the glory.
Soli Deo Gloria.

